This aims to be an Objective-C wrapper around the Cairo 2D graphics library

Building

Mac OS X

Install cairo-devel and gnustep-make-cocoa via MacPorts

sudo port install cairo-devel +macosx +no_x11
sudo port install gnustep-make-cocoa

make

Windows

Install GNUstep

[Insert link here]

Install Cairo

http://inkscape.modevia.com/win32libs/
http://inkscape.modevia.com/win32libs/cairo-1.6.4-mingw.tar.gz
Note: the file above is actually a bzip2 archive

Extract the cairo archive into your GNUstep root. This is probably best done via
cygwin. E.g.

tar --strip-components=2 --show-transformed-names -jxvf /path/to/cairo-1.6.4-mingw.tar.gz

Run make from within a GNUstep shell
make -f GNUmakefile.win
